oe-caos
----------------------------------------
this folder contains the layer for build caOS with open-embedded 

Have to do:

source ./bootstrap.sh  < destination build path>  <full path of open-embedded toplayer >

to install openembededd:


1)sudo apt-get install gawk wget git-core diffstat unzip texinfo gcc-multilib \
    build-essential chrpath libsdl1.2-dev xterm

2) git clone git://git.openembedded.org/openembedded-core oe-core
3)cd oe-core
4)git clone git://git.openembedded.org/bitbake bitbake

to build caos

1)git clone https://github.com/ataima/oe-caos.git oe-caos
2)cd oe-caos
3) source ./bootstrap.sh <full path of build caos directory > < full path of oe-core >
4) when bitbake ended into <full path of build caos directory >/image/ the result :
caOS.bin file